To run Locokit:

1) ifconfig

you will see:
something like this:

lo        Link encap:Local Loopback  
          inet addr:127.0.0.1  Mask:255.0.0.0
          inet6 addr: ::1/128 Scope:Host
          UP LOOPBACK RUNNING  MTU:65536  Metric:1
          RX packets:1451 errors:0 dropped:0 overruns:0 frame:0
          TX packets:1451 errors:0 dropped:0 overruns:0 carrier:0
          collisions:0 txqueuelen:0 
          RX bytes:132292 (132.2 KB)  TX bytes:132292 (132.2 KB)

wlan1     Link encap:Ethernet  HWaddr 40:f0:2f:4f:3c:f9  
          inet addr:192.168.2.3  Bcast:192.168.2.255  Mask:255.255.255.0
          inet6 addr: fe80::42f0:2fff:fe4f:3cf9/64 Scope:Link
          UP BROADCAST RUNNING MULTICAST  MTU:1500  Metric:1
          RX packets:15539 errors:0 dropped:0 overruns:0 frame:41429
          TX packets:11061 errors:0 dropped:0 overruns:0 carrier:0
          collisions:0 txqueuelen:1000 
          RX bytes:19216759 (19.2 MB)  TX bytes:1498472 (1.4 MB)
          Interrupt:19 


2) open connectionToLocokit

make sure that you have the variable "wlan1" in there everywhere 


#1. Stop network manager para que no cambie a eduroam
service network-manager stop

#2. apagar el wifi
ifconfig wlan1 down

#3. configurar la red de locokit
iwconfig wlan1 mode ad-hoc essid locokit02 #cambiar por el nombre de red de cada locokit

#4. configurar la ip de tu ordenador en la red
ifconfig wlan1 192.168.2.3				

#5. Arrancar el wifi otra vez
ifconfig wlan1 up


3) then run the file "connectionToLocokit"
poma@poma-HP-EliteBook-840-G1:~/workspace/pmanoonpong-gorobots-fork/projects/locokit/footsensor$ sudo ./connectionToLocokit 

It will display
stop: Unknown instance: 


4) then open web browser and type "http://192.168.2.2/"

5) insert motor IDs into the web 11,8,6,46

6) set motor command


-------------------------------------------------

Running the code on Locokit


1) poma@poma-HP-EliteBook-840-G1:~/workspace/pmanoonpong-gorobots-fork/projects/locokit/footsensor$ ssh root@192.168.2.2

2) password: enter

3) root@overo:~# 

--> go to AitorTests  --> py

4) root@overo:~/AitorTests/py# 

To run the gallop gait
root@overo:~/AitorTests/py# python gallop.py

5) To stop 
root@overo:~/AitorTests/py# python stop.py

Note, if you change the wheel, then you have to change the angle setting:

6) nano gallop.py


actuatorID = [8,11,6,46]
correction = [0, 0, 0, 0]
actuatorDefase = [180,180,0,270] // angle setting!!!!!
actuatorDirection = [0,1,0,1] // direction 
period= 1 // set speed


